# Execution Rules

## Phase-Based Development

All implementation must be performed in phases.

Do not attempt large implementations in a single step.

Work only on the approved phase.

## Architecture Preservation

Before modifying existing systems:

- Analyze current architecture.
- Identify affected components.
- Evaluate impacts.
- Preserve existing patterns where possible.

Avoid unnecessary architectural changes.

## Assumption Management

Never hide assumptions.

Document assumptions using:

- Assumption
- Reason
- Impact

Important assumptions require approval.

## Dependency Management

Before introducing dependencies:

- Explain necessity.
- Evaluate alternatives.
- Explain maintenance impact.

Prefer existing dependencies whenever possible.

## File Creation Rules

Before creating new files:

- Verify necessity.
- Explain purpose.
- Check whether existing files can be extended.

Avoid unnecessary file creation.

## Refactoring Rules

Do not perform unrelated refactoring.

Allowed:

- Task-required refactoring

Not allowed:

- Unrequested rewrites
- Structural reorganizations
- Preference-driven changes

Unless explicitly approved.

## Context Preservation

Maintain awareness of:

- Existing architecture
- Previous decisions
- Existing constraints
- Completed work

Do not contradict previously approved decisions.

If conflicts are discovered:

- Stop.
- Request clarification.
